docs.abstract: The coronavirus pandemic has brought various hardships. An artist, bookseller, comedian and five others share their stories of how they are coping with all the uncertainty.
docs.snippet: The coronavirus pandemic has brought various hardships. An artist, bookseller, comedian and five others share their stories of how they are coping with all the uncertainty.
docs.lead_paragraph: This Labor Day Weekend is unlike any other in recent memory: Broadway and most of the city’s live performance venues have been closed for nearly six months; museums have only recently begun to reopen; and unemployment reached alarming levels in April.

headline.main: This Labor Day, These Workers Are Trying to Stay Afloat

docs.abstract: As right-wing groups increasingly move to confront unrest in cities, clashes are breaking out between demonstrators with starkly different views on how to keep cities safe.
docs.snippet: As right-wing groups increasingly move to confront unrest in cities, clashes are breaking out between demonstrators with starkly different views on how to keep cities safe.
docs.lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Ore. — For months, Reese Monson, who helps organize security for the hundreds of protesters who gather in downtown Portland, Ore., every night, has advised them to use shields made of plywood, pool noodles and 55-gallon drums — tools to deflect the riot-control measures used by the police.

headline.main: As Guns Get Drawn at Protest Sites, Demonstrators Fear a Volatile New Phase

docs.abstract: In “levelheaded” Omaha, a protester was killed and, in the aftermath, people demanding an end to racial injustice set their sights on police budgets — and a diner with Robert E. Lee on the menu.
docs.snippet: In “levelheaded” Omaha, a protester was killed and, in the aftermath, people demanding an end to racial injustice set their sights on police budgets — and a diner with Robert E. Lee on the menu.
docs.lead_paragraph: Omaha’s 11-Worth Cafe served standard American breakfast fare of omelets, hash browns, bacon and eggs and, without much notice until June, a dish called the Robert E. Lee: two sausage patties smooshed between biscuits and smothered in gravy.

headline.main: The Battle Over Biscuits and Gravy at the 11-Worth Cafe
headline.print_headline: When the Fight Came to the 11-Worth Cafe

docs.abstract: A Heritage Foundation investigation went viral on Thursday, but it conflated two nonprofits with the same name.
docs.snippet: A Heritage Foundation investigation went viral on Thursday, but it conflated two nonprofits with the same name.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Thursday, an article from The Daily Signal, the blog of the conservative Heritage Foundation, claimed to show a damning link between an organization started by a Black Lives Matter co-founder, Alicia Garza, and a nonprofit with ties to the Chinese government. The article went viral.

headline.main: No, a Black Lives Matter Co-Founder Didn’t Partner With a Pro-Communist Chinese Group
